<raw><![CDATA[ BERLIN, Dec 15 (Reuters) - European Union leaders will adopta deal on a rescue shield for the euro zone when they meet at asummit on Thursday and Friday, German Chancellor Angela Merkelsaid on Wednesday. Merkel said the leaders would adopt the deal struck latelast month by their finance ministers, who agreed to create theEuropean Stabilisation Mechanism (ESM) -- a permanent mechanismfor resolving sovereign debt crises -- from mid-2013.[ID:nLDE6AS05Z] (Reporting by Dave Graham and Brian Rohan, writing by PaulCarrel)             ]]></raw>
